description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking for new opportunities to make a contribution and develop your skills?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you committed to working within a multi-professional team across two counties?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you have energy, skills and enthusiasm to support those with personality disorders in a responsive way that meets their needs?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen in The Complex Needs Service for a Team Therapist, on a 12 month fixed term contract. We provide a cross county network of services for people who have severe emotional or mental health difficulties sometimes described as ‘personality disorder’ or ‘complex needs’. Complex Needs Service operates across Oxfordshire and Buckinghamshire and you will be expected to work from locations in both counties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers the opportunity to gain experience in working in a psychotherapeutic service offering intensive group work within Therapeutic Community and other models. The successful applicant will need to have a core mental health qualification and/or psychotherapy qualification and experience in assessment and risk assessment processes. If you have the enthusiasm and commitment we can support your personal growth and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews are carried out in 3 parts to enable service users and staff to meet the candidates. Candidates are expected to attend all 3 parts. Due to COVID some of these will be carried out using MS Teams and Zoom.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameGill AttwoodJob titleTeam LeaderEmail addressgillian.attwood@oxfordhealth.nhs.ukTelephone number01865 904300&lt;/p&gt;
